01:00:09.954 --> 01:00:30.593
Incoming livestream: Where you're just looking at accuracy, precision, recall, and F-score. And then when people sort of stare into these statistics, they sort of get into disagreement about whether, well, is it the model that's wrong, or are the labels wrong? The labels are really noisy, which is basically always the case. Or you could be in this different world, right, where you're looking at many different dimensions at once, all of which are somewhat noisy, but together give you a much more complete picture of whether your system's actually working.


